video.description:
_READ ME_
With the recent release of The Last of Us 2 video game, came a few lovely and unexpected covers. I heard this one, and immediately wanted to learn how to play and sing it! I kept this version very simple and honest - totally imperfect! I'm not a guitarist, but am grateful for a few chords in my pocket..! Warts and all...

If you'd like... I want to invite you to try singing or playing this song, or a simple song of your choosing, finding a few minutes in your day just for you and your music - no big agenda, just for you. (For the broadcasters - tag me on insta etc if you love sharing! Though really this is just about you and your music, no presh)
We can often think that complicated/clever/showy music is more impactful, but what about those memories of a guitar, a campfire and a familiar voice? The song your mother used to sing to help you sleep, or a favourite jingle on the radio...? 
Don't get me wrong, I love bells, whistles and the rest of it - but there is something comfortingly human in the more humble renditions. Special, intangible and important.
Tough maybe you're a big-gig-guy, or a peng-production-prince - nice!!
But I bet you'll still hum Hallelujah with Jeff, or whisper Martha with Waits. 
Who doesn't love nostalgia? ;) 

This is really a video for TLOU2 fans and might not make much sense outside of the (intense!) storyline...  but if you've watched this and you don't know what I'm talking about - thanks for sticking around anyway!

I always say it, and it's taking a while.... but there is MORE coming soon - consider this a seasonal nibble. 

Thanks again, you lot of wonderfuls x
